-- Panthers Sign Career Touchdown Leader Steve Smith to 3-Year Deal
-- B y   L a r r y   S i d d o n s
-- 2012-04-10T15:57:43Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-04-10/panthers-sign-career-touchdown-leader-steve-smith-to-3-year-deal.html
The Carolina Panthers signed a
three-year contract extension with wide receiver  Steve Smith ,
the team’s career touchdown leader.  Financial terms weren’t disclosed in a news release from
the National Football League club.  Smith has spent his entire 11-year NFL career with the
Panthers, scoring 67 touchdowns and catching 699 passes for
10,278 yards, all franchise marks. Last season, he became the
35th player in NFL history with 10,000 receiving yards and has
caught at least one pass in 75 straight games since 2006,
according to the release.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Larry Siddons at 
 lsiddons@bloomberg.net  